  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the role of Cooperative in poverty alleviation of small holding fruit growers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project plan for 2020 are as follows1.link to market2.shareholding structure design3.incentives for management team4.lobby to government agencies</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strenthened governance and leadership</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Yinfu Fruit Cooperative was founded on 2012 by 186  fruitgrowers. Yinfu cooperative got support from China Foundation of Poverty Alleviation (CFPA) and MercyCorps since 2016. CFPA and Mercy Corps helped Yinfu Cooperative on cold store and supply chain management  mainly on marketing and sales of cherry via online channels. The hope was that by boosting cherry  sales  the cooperative can recognise the importance of sound governance to cooperative and started to change the governance structure of one person deciding for the rest. The desired change on governance  however  did not take place. Agriterra was invited to work on the cooperative&#x2019;s deep-rooted governance issues in 2020. For this one-year project  Agriterra&#x2019;s focus has been on ownership structure. Innovatively Agriterra proposed three types of shares that the cooperative could issue. The first one was common shares for members  with which each member must hold at least one share. Another type of share was special shares for members  with which members are free to subscribe. The third type was special shares for non-members. The village cooperative has subscribed 300k CNY into Yinfu Cooperative  for the purpose of dividend benefits. The village cooperative was expected the shares could bring dividends for at least 3 years for the villagers  especially for the poor ones.By introducing these three types of share  the current governance structure needs to be reformed. The principles of democratic control  one member  one vote was introduced. Board and supervisory board were re-elected. Member commitments was expected to rise.</narrative>
  </description>
